Rating: 4
These were a perfect accompaniment to a roast tenderloin with wine sauce. You can do part of this recipe ahead of time and then finish it at the last minute. I sauteed the shitake mushrooms a couple of hours in advance and set them aside. I also prepared the shallots, etc, ahead, then put the chicken stock and green beans in the pot and left them there --ready to go-- until my tenderloin was ready. While the tenderloin was resting, I turned on the stove and finished the dish. Easy. It was very well received at my dinner party -- but be sure to season it to taste.

