Rating: 4
Amazing that somethiong so simple could be so good. I changed the proportions slightly, for two servings using five ounces haricots verts, 3 ounces shiitakes, 1 shallot, skipped garlic, 1 teaspoon butter and 1 1/2 teaspoons olive oil total, and the whole 2/3 cup low salt chicken broth. Because the haricots verts take so much less time to cook, I kept my medium skilllet uncovered and they were tender with the broth mostly gone in 4-5 minutes. Super good!

